title: A plane hit a kangaroo during takeoff in Australia
text:
A plane hit a kangaroo during takeoff in Australia Last updated 14:37, July 30 2015 Flickr 
An early morning domestic flight in Australia had to be cancelled when the plane hit a kangaroo (not pictured). 
A REX flight from the New South Wales-Victorian border town of Mildura in Australia was cancelled after the plane hit a kangaroo on the runway during a pre-dawn takeoff today. 
Flight ZL3653 was taxiing down the runway at about 6.30am, bound for Melbourne, when it hit the kangaroo. 
A spokesperson for the regional airline was unsure whether the animal was killed. Mildura to Melb flight cancelled after plane struck kangaroo during take-off. REX says it was dark when roo was hit on runway. Prpellor dmgd â€” Tom Maddocks (@MaddocksThomas) July 30, 2015 
It was dark at the time when the kangaroo was hit by the right propeller. The plane is now being repaired. 
Passengers on the flight were transferred to another aircraft.
